* Iron Raptor keeps looking towards the armor-clad Iris, still thinking that 
it was rather strange that one moment she remembered her as a star on a 
scrren...and now she was this warrior looking bot standing less then 100 
meters away.

Suddenly she gets a hint of just what Shadow was doing from Prowl, looking 
towards him as he fires.
A fight was in hand, was it?
Well, if Shadow wanted a fight she was sure that Prowl and herself could 
give him one!

Iris also saw Shadow, then looking towards Iron Raptor.*

IRIS: " Don't let that pinfeather of a boyfriend of yours push you around 
this time!"

* She yelled outloud, Iron Raptor rolling her eyes and then looking over 
towards Prowl as he sends two missiles towards the enemy.
But there was something that she couldn't understand: Just what was this 
Shadow's problem anyway? Was he a Pred? Alliance?
Anyway, he was going down!

Iron Raptor turned and faced Shadow, feeling her muscles tighten as she 
looked at him.
Would her body react on it's own again, leaving her mind to catch up when it 
was all over...again?
There was only one way to find out.
Iron Raptor looked at Prowl for a sec.*

< Ofcourse, I wouldn't like it any other WAY!!>

* With that she felt her body shift, just the same as it had when it moved 
on it's own the first time.
Only...only she had a feeling that she might be able to controle it this 
time.
Iron Raptor pounded her feet in two quick steps towards Shadow before she 
removed her sword from behind her head in one fluid motion, the blade 
glowing for a sec, then bringing it down in one smooth slash, sending an 
energy slash towards Shadow.
But then she brought up her hand again, leaving the sword to point up 
stright in the air with her arms straight as well...and another e-slash sent 
towards the enemy.*
